abstract: Melania Trump on Monday cited the influence of “Achy Breaky Heart” singer Billy Ray Cyrus as she asked spouses of the nation's governors to address cyberassault in their states.
snippet: Melania Trump on Monday cited the influence of “Achy Breaky Heart” singer Billy Ray Cyrus as she asked spouses of the nation's governors to address cyberassault in their states.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Melania Trump on Monday cited the influence of “Achy Breaky Heart” singer Billy Ray Cyrus as she asked spouses of the nation's governors to address cyberassault in their states.
headline_main: Melania Trump Asks Governors' Spouses to Tackle Cyberassault
headline_print_headline: Melania Trump Asks Governors' Spouses to Tackle Cyberassault

abstract: The White House budget released on Monday proposed cutting funding for the U.S. government-owned passenger rail carrier Amtrak while calling for a significant hike in infrastructure spending and killing a clean energy auto loan program.
snippet: The White House budget released on Monday proposed cutting funding for the U.S. government-owned passenger rail carrier Amtrak while calling for a significant hike in infrastructure spending and killing a clean energy auto loan program.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The White House budget released on Monday proposed cutting funding for the U.S. government-owned passenger rail carrier Amtrak while calling for a significant hike in infrastructure spending and killing a clean energy auto loan program.
headline_main: Trump Proposes Cutting Amtrak Funding, Boosting Infrastructure Spending
headline_print_headline: Trump Proposes Cutting Amtrak Funding, Boosting Infrastructure Spending

abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump's $740.5 billion defense budget request sent to Congress on Monday includes more money for nuclear weapons and a big boost to research and development spending to prepare for future warfare.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. President Donald Trump's $740.5 billion defense budget request sent to Congress on Monday includes more money for nuclear weapons and a big boost to research and development spending to prepare for future warfare.
headline_main: Trump's Pentagon Budget Bolsters Nuclear Weapons, Weapons Research

abstract: Workers can’t return to their jobs as supply lines get snarled, extending the forced holiday and fracturing the country.
snippet: Workers can’t return to their jobs as supply lines get snarled, extending the forced holiday and fracturing the country.
lead_paragraph: Workers are stuck in their hometowns. Officials want detailed health plans before factories or offices can reopen. Assembly lines that make General Motors cars and Apple iPhones are standing silent.

abstract: A man charged with driving a van into a tent where local Republicans were registering voters worked as a stagehand and had lived in northeast Florida for two years, according to jail records and an arrest report.
snippet: A man charged with driving a van into a tent where local Republicans were registering voters worked as a stagehand and had lived in northeast Florida for two years, according to jail records and an arrest report.
lead_paragraph: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. — A man charged with driving a van into a tent where local Republicans were registering voters worked as a stagehand and had lived in northeast Florida for two years, according to jail records and an arrest report.
headline_main: Man Who Drove Van at GOP Voter Sign-Up Worked as Stagehand
headline_print_headline: Man Who Drove Van at GOP Voter Sign-Up Worked as Stagehand

abstract: Facing significant legal challenges, the Trump administration has disbanded its advisory board created to help boost trophy hunting and relax federal rules for importing the heads and hides of African elephants, lions and rhinos.
snippet: Facing significant legal challenges, the Trump administration has disbanded its advisory board created to help boost trophy hunting and relax federal rules for importing the heads and hides of African elephants, lions and rhinos.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Facing significant legal challenges, the Trump administration has disbanded its advisory board created to help boost trophy hunting and relax federal rules for importing the heads and hides of African elephants, lions and rhinos.
headline_main: Interior Dept. Drops Trophy Hunting Council Amid Court Fight
headline_print_headline: Interior Dept. Drops Trophy Hunting Council Amid Court Fight

abstract: The U.S. government's top counterintelligence official said Monday that he was concerned Russia or other foreign adversaries could exploit the chaos of the Iowa caucuses to sow distrust in the integrity of America's elections.

abstract: A U.S. Justice Department anti-human trafficking grant program is facing internal complaints, after two nonprofits were denied funding in favor of two less established groups whose applications were not recommended by career DOJ officials.
